# JWT Auth Microservice

This is a sample microservice built with Node.js that demonstrates JWT authentication. It provides an API endpoint that requires JWT authentication to access data from an external API(https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users).

## Features

- JWT authentication using a secret key
- Forwarding the JWT token to an external API
- Issuer based authorization

## Prerequisites

- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- npm or yarn package manager

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository:

```shell
git clone <repository_url>
```
2. Install the dependencies:
```shell
cd jwt-auth-microservice
npm install
```
3. Set the Secret Key:
Replace 'your-secret-key' in the secrets/secret.js file with your own secret key.

4. Start the microservice:
npm start
The microservice will start running on http://localhost:3000.

5. To Test the microservice
- Import the postman collection and environment under /collections
- Replace the secret key with the one provided in secret.js
